<h2 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin: 0 0 8px 0;">
  Email Preview
</h2>

<table role="presentation" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
  <tr>
    <td style="background-color: #eff6ff; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; text-align: center;">
      <p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1e40af; margin: 0 0 8px 0;">
        This is a test email
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 13px; color: #3b82f6; margin: 0;">
        Email type: <strong><%= @email_type.to_s.humanize %></strong>
      </p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #374151; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
  This confirms that your email configuration is working correctly.
  When this email type is triggered, it will be sent with your business name
  <strong>"<%= @business_name.presence || "(not set)" %>"</strong> in the header.
</p>

<p style="font-size: 13px; color: #6b7280; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">
  Here's what each email type does:
</p>

<table role="presentation" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
  <tr>
    <td style="padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #f3f4f6;">
      <p style="font-size: 13px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 2px 0;">Payment Reminder</p>
      <p style="font-size: 12px; color: #6b7280; margin: 0;">Sent to borrowers before a payment is due</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #f3f4f6;">
      <p style="font-size: 13px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 2px 0;">Late Payment Notice</p>
      <p style="font-size: 12px; color: #6b7280; margin: 0;">Sent to borrowers when a payment is overdue</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #f3f4f6;">
      <p style="font-size: 13px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 2px 0;">Payment Receipt</p>
      <p style="font-size: 12px; color: #6b7280; margin: 0;">Sent to borrowers when a payment is recorded</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="padding: 12px 0;">
      <p style="font-size: 13px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 2px 0;">Monthly Summary</p>
      <p style="font-size: 12px; color: #6b7280; margin: 0;">Sent to you on the 1st of each month with portfolio stats</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p style="font-size: 12px; color: #9ca3af; margin: 0;">
  You can enable or disable each email type in your Settings page.
</p>
